This will not work, because `endObject(par)` negates the comparison. The following would be an option:

```
if (rootNativeField && !endObject(par)) {
    par.nextToken();
}
```

But this is a bit confusing to read and it leads to a `par.nextToken()` call if the current token is null. I think this is not wanted.
A new `OpenRtbJsonUtils` helper method would be an alternative, like :

```
public static boolean isEndObject(JsonParser par) {   
  return par.hasCurrentToken() && par.getCurrentToken() == JsonToken.END_OBJECT;
}
```

This could then be used in `readNativeRequest` and `readNativeResponse`, like:

```
if (rootNativeField && isEndObject(par)) {
    par.nextToken();
}
```

What do you think?

